results.name: Missing Maps: Teknaf, Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh (2)
results.shortDescription:
`Intermediate mappers and Validation needed. Please only map in JOSM!`

- Author: **Missing Maps**
- Requesting Organization: **British Red Cross**


The Bangladesh Red Crescent Society (BDRCS) and British Red Cross (BRC) are partnering to support community Resilience through a Vulnerability to Resilience (V2R) programme in Teknaf, Cox's Bazar.

The V2R programme will take a multi sector approach with the aim that communities in Teknaf including locals and dispersed guest households live in harmony and that people have the capacity to meet their basic needs and deal with risks to enable their safety. The programme will also focus on mainstreaming protection, including enhancing awareness of human trafficking, and support BDRCS to better respond the emerging risks and hazards.

The map data will be used as a basemap to then add and improve infrastructure data in the communities. This data will be collected via a mobile survey. The improved OSM basemap will improve the accuracy when adding the new features and its use in resilience programming.

results.name: DRC/Bundibugyo District Border Mapping
results.shortDescription:
Author: Missing Maps / HOT Uganda
* Requesting organization:  HOT Uganda/UNHCR
### Imagery: Esri World Imagery
The escalation of violence in DRC  has led to 48,105 refugees arriving in Uganda since January 2018. This rapidly developing situation is not helped by the Ebola outbreak in the DRC. It is vital that accurate and up-to-date mapping information is available to allow UNHCR and partners to respond to needs more effectively and efficiently.

results.name: Missing Maps: Embu county, Kenya (2)
results.shortDescription:
MSF is supporting health centres in Embu County in Kenya to develop a model of care for Non Communicable Diseases such as diabetes or epilepsy. In order to have a good understanding of the area of interest of the project, it would be valuable to have a high detailed map of the county. 

This map would help the team to know the accessibility to the health facilities (as it is planned to support more next year) as well as their catchment area. The OpenStreetMap community can help by digitalizing the roads and main landmarks and the teams on site will collect more precise information such as villages names or health facilities locations.
